<task id="DEVOPS-001" project="Spaarke DevOps Project Tracking r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extend GitHub Project #2 Type field with Project option</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <tags>github-project, schema, foundation, gh-cli</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>P1-schema</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
Add a new `Project` option to the `Type` single-select field on GitHub Project #2 ("Spaarke Core") at https://github.com/users/spaarke-dev/projects/2. The existing options (`Idea`, `Epic`, `Story`, `Task`, `Bug`, `Spike`) MUST be preserved. After this lands, the field offers 7 options total. This is a hand-driven Phase 1 task; the `/devops-portfolio-setup` skill (task 010) will codify this for idempotent re-run.
  </prompt>

  <role>
DevOps engineer fluent with GitHub Projects v2 GraphQL API + `gh` CLI v2.40+. You operate within an authenticated `gh auth status` session as `spaarke-dev`.
  </role>

  <goal>
`gh project field-list 2 --owner spaarke-dev --format json` shows the `Type` field options list now including `"name":"Project"` alongside the 6 existing options. No existing item's `Type` value has been altered.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST use `gh` CLI (or `gh api graphql`) â€” no Octokit/REST wrapper</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST preserve all existing Type options; this is additive only</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">Project #2 is the only portfolio surface â€” no new board</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">Idempotency target â€” re-running this task on an already-extended schema MUST be a no-op</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/design.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="gh GraphQL update single-select field" location="https://docs.github.com/en/issues/planning-and-tracking-with-projects/automating-your-project/using-the-api-to-manage-projects">
        Use `updateProjectV2Field` mutation with `singleSelectOptions` to add an option. Get the field ID via `gh project field-list 2 --owner spaarke-dev --format json | jq` first.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check">Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-01 section. Verify `gh auth status` is active as `spaarke-dev`.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Capture baseline">Run `gh project field-list 2 --owner spaarke-dev --format json` and save output to `notes/spikes/phase1-baseline-fields-{date}.json`. Confirm Type field ID + existing options. Note item count.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Idempotency pre-check">Inspect baseline JSON. If `"name":"Project"` already exists in Type options, REPORT no-op and exit early (this is the idempotency contract).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Compose mutation">Build the `updateProjectV2Field` GraphQL mutation that ADDS `Project` to existing `singleSelectOptions` (must include ALL existing options to avoid wiping them; the mutation replaces the full list).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Execute mutation">Run via `gh api graphql -f query='...' -f projectId=... -f fieldId=... -f options=...`. Capture response.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify">Re-run `gh project field-list 2 --owner spaarke-dev --format json`. Confirm `Type` now has 7 options including `Project`; confirm no existing option lost.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify items untouched">Spot-check 3 existing items: their `Type` value should be unchanged.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Document">Save final field JSON to `notes/spikes/phase1-after-fr01-{date}.json`. Update task status in TASK-INDEX.md.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="gh">GitHub CLI for Project mutations</tool>
    <tool name="jq">JSON parsing (Windows: `winget install jq` or use PowerShell `ConvertFrom-Json`)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="config">GitHub Project #2 Type field â€” 7 options total</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/notes/spikes/phase1-baseline-fields-{date}.json</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/notes/spikes/phase1-after-fr01-{date}.json</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`gh project field-list 2 --owner spaarke-dev --format json | jq '.fields[] | select(.name=="Type") | .options[].name'` includes `Project`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Existing 6 Type options (`Idea`, `Epic`, `Story`, `Task`, `Bug`, `Spike`) still present</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No existing item's Type value changed (random spot-check of 3 items)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Re-running the task is a no-op (idempotency dry-run reports zero proposed mutations)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
